1  sudo apt-get install zsh
2  install the oh-myzsh
3  you must want to use the shell plugins
https://travis.media/top-10-oh-my-zsh-plugins-for-productive-developers/#20210719-history
4  the history search is usefull
https://github.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh/tree/master/plugins/history
5  the autojump is usefull
https://github.com/wting/autojump
6  zsh-syntax-highlighting is usefull
https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-syntax-highlighting
